The paper deals with optimization problems related to graphs and combinatorics, specifically in the context of cancer genomics. The paper mentions several well-studied notions in combinatorial optimization, such as chain partitions in partially ordered sets, laminar hypergraphs, and colorings of graphs. These topics are typically covered in the arXiv sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Combinatorics (cs.CC), and Graph Theory (cs.GT). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
